>> title: Hot Chicken Tenders (Dave's Style)
>> cuisine: American
>> tags: kid-friendly, teaching, fried
>> servings: 2

-- Nashville hot chicken the way Dave's does it: brined tenders, shaggy
-- crust, and the heat painted on at the end so EACH PERSON PICKS THEIR OWN
-- LEVEL. The lessons: dredging, fry safety, and cooking to temperature.
-- ADULT ON OIL DUTY. Start the brine the night before.

The night before (or morning of): in a #bowl{}, stir @buttermilk{1%cup}, @pickle juice{1/4%cup}(from the pickle jar), @hot sauce{2%tbsp}, and @kosher salt{1%tsp}. Add @chicken tenders{1 1/4%lb}, cover, and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

Set up the dredge: in a shallow #dish{}, whisk @all-purpose flour{1 1/2%cups}, @cornstarch{1/4%cup}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @kosher salt{1%tsp}, and @black pepper{1/2%tsp}. Drizzle in 2 tbsp of the brine and toss with a fork - those little clumps become the shaggy, crunchy bits.

Dredge each tender: out of the brine, into the flour, PRESS the flour on hard, back in the brine for a quick dip, then into the flour again. Double-dredged = extra crust. Set on a rack for 10 minutes so the coating sets.

Heat @vegetable oil{3%cups} (about 1/2 inch deep) in a heavy #skillet{} to 350F on a #thermometer{}. Fry safety: tenders go in AWAY from you, no crowding (two batches), and the adult handles the pan.

Fry 3-4 minutes per side until deep golden and 165F inside - temp it, don't guess. Rest on a clean rack.

Make the hot oil: CAREFULLY ladle @vegetable oil{1/4%cup} of the hot frying oil into a metal #bowl{}. Whisk in @brown sugar{1%tbsp}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}, and @cayenne pepper{2%tsp} to taste. Heat ladder, Dave's style - No Spice: skip the cayenne. Lite: 1 tsp. Medium: 2 tsp. Hot: 1 tbsp. Mix a separate small bowl per heat level and brush each person's tenders with their own.

Serve on @white bread{4%slices} with @dill pickles{8%slices} on top.

-- Owen picks his level. Dad, don't be a hero.
